modules.description: Converts between bit vector representations and S-expressions. Works with `Bitvec_sexp.t` and `Sexplib0.Sexp.t` types. Useful for serializing and deserializing bit vectors to and from human-readable S-expressions, particularly in configuration or data exchange contexts.

This module enables serialization and deserialization of bit vectors to S-expressions, supporting data persistence and structured text-based communication. It defines `sexp_of_t` and `t_of_sexp` for converting `Bitvec.t` values to and from `Sexplib0.Sexp.t` representations. For example, you can use `sexp_of_t` to write a bit vector to a configuration file or `t_of_sexp` to reconstruct it from a serialized S-expression. The module directly provides these core conversion functions while aligning with the Sexp library for parsing and generating structured text.
